Package infodynamics.measures.continuous.gaussian

Class MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorGaussian

  • java.lang.Object
    • infodynamics.measures.continuous.MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon
      • infodynamics.measures.continuous.gaussian.MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorGaussian
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InfoMeasureCalculatorContinuous
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DualTotalCorrelationCalculatorGaussian, OInfoCalculatorGaussian, SInfoCalculatorGaussian
    public abstract class MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorGaussian
extends MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon

    Base class with common functionality for child class implementations of multivariate information measures on a given multivariate double[][] set of observations (extending MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon), assuming that the probability distribution function for these observations is a multivariate Gaussian distribution.

    Usage is as per the paradigm outlined for MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon, with:

    • For constructors see the child classes.
    • Further properties are defined in MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon.setProperty(String, String).
    • Computed values are in nats, not bits!

    References:

    • Rosas, F., Mediano, P., Gastpar, M, Jensen, H., "Quantifying high-order interdependencies via multivariate extensions of the mutual information", Physical Review E 100, (2019) 032305.
    Author:
    Pedro A.M. Mediano (email, www)

        public void setCovarianceAndMeans​(double[][] covariance,
                                  double[] means)
                           throws java.lang.Exception

        Set the covariance of the distribution for which we will compute the measure.

        This is an alternative to sequences of calls to MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon.setObservations(double[][]) or MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon.addObservations(double[][]) etc. Note that without setting any observations, you cannot later call MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon.computeLocalOfPreviousObservations().

        Parameters:
        covariance - covariance matrix of the system
        means - mean of the system
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • setCovariance

        public void setCovariance​(double[][] cov,
                          boolean covFromObservations)
                   throws java.lang.Exception

        Set the covariance of the distribution for which we will compute the measure.

        This is an alternative to sequences of calls to MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon.setObservations(double[][]) or MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon.addObservations(double[][]) etc. Note that without setting any observations, you cannot later call MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon.computeLocalOfPreviousObservations(), and without providing the means of the variables, you cannot later call MultiVariateInfoMeasureCalculatorCommon.computeLocalUsingPreviousObservations(double[][]).

        Parameters:
        covariance - covariance matrix of the system
        covFromObservations - whether the covariance matrix was determined internally from observations or not
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - for covariance matrix not matching the expected dimensions, being non-square, asymmetric or non-positive definite
